; Several tree-sitter grammar npm packages declare conflicting peer-deps
; on different `tree-sitter` major versions (e.g. tree-sitter-cpp wants
; ^0.21.1 while tree-sitter-c-sharp wants ^0.25.0). projscan loads them
; as wasm at runtime and never imports the native `tree-sitter` package,
; so the peer conflict is benign — but plain `npm ci` rejects it.
; legacy-peer-deps=true makes the install resolve like npm v6 (warn,
; don't fail) and matches the local-dev experience.
legacy-peer-deps=true
